OL,3,CAre Holiday homes being mis-sold with
OL,4,Cbuyers misled?
OL,6,FTonight spoke to a wide range of
OL,7,Fpeople and built up an eye opening
OL,8,Fpicture of the holiday park industry.
OL,9,FA number of people said they were too
OL,10,Fscared to speak out publicly and some
OL,11,Fwere legally bound to silence having
OL,12,Fsigned confidentiality clauses as part
OL,13,Fof settlements.
OL,15,FThe main complaint that comes up time
OL,16,Fand again: people saying they've
OL,17,Frecouped just a fraction of what they
OL,18,Foriginally paid for their holiday home
OL,19,Fwhen they come to sell it, leaving
OL,20,Fthem financially and emotionally
OL,21,Fdevastated.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
