OL,3,CAre Holiday homes being mis-sold with
OL,4,Cbuyers misled?
OL,6,F"Holiday parks are an unregulated
OL,7,Fsector. There is no regulator who
OL,8,Fcontrols them or ensures that they
OL,9,Fbehave a certain way. What does apply
OL,10,Fthough is consumer law. We do have
OL,11,Fthings like the Consumer Rights Act
OL,12,Fthat means that terms in any of the
OL,13,Fcontracts must be fair. We've got
OL,14,Fconsumer protection from unfair
OL,15,Ftrading regulations and we have the
OL,16,FMisrepresentation Act. So all of these
OL,17,Fthings are things that can be enforced
OL,18,Fagainst parks if they missell. The
OL,19,Fproblem is that sometimes taking an
OL,20,Forganization to court, particularly an
OL,21,Forganization with deep pockets, can be
OL,22,Fquite daunting. It can be expensive,
OL,23,Fespecially if you have to go and seek
OL,24,Flegal advice" - Lisa Webb, Consumer
OL,25,FExpert, Which?
